700026f-a.text:
East 132nd Street, north side, east from (No. 679) but not including Cypress Ave. In the background, across the elevated trestle of the New York, New Haven and Hartford Railroad, is visible the power plant of the United Electric Light and Power Co., on the East River shore.
April 12, 1931
P. L. Sperr

700027f-a.text:
East 132nd Street, north side, west from (No. 703) a point east
of Cypress Ave.
April 12, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

700841f-b.text:
(1)
Cypress Ave. (extreme left), north from East 132nd Street (foreground), showing the clearance, on the east side of the avenue, created for the construction of an approach to the Triborough Bridge. lIt extends to East 135th Street. In the left foreground is the Jacob Doll piano
factory.
September 26, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Part of the same (extreme right center in View 1), as viewed eastward.
September 26, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same as view 1, at a later date.
